-- в”Ђв”Ђ Tropic в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Tropic is an AI-powered procurement and vendor management platform that helps finance and procurement teams benchmark software pricing, automate renewals, and control SaaS spend.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE(NULL, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2020, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$New York, New York, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Tropic Review: AI Procurement and SaaS Spend Management$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Tropic is an AI procurement platform for benchmarking software prices, automating renewals, and cutting SaaS spend. See features, pricing model, and pros.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Tropic is an intelligent procurement and spend management platform founded in 2020 by Justin Etkin and David Campbell, headquartered in New York City. The company emerged from stealth in April 2020 with a 2.1 million dollar seed round and has since raised a total of 67.1 million dollars across multiple rounds from investors including Insight Partners, Canaan, and Founder Collective, including a 25 million dollar round reported by TechCrunch in August 2021. Tropic's platform combines three capabilities: proprietary price-benchmarking intelligence drawn from over 100,000 analyzed software deals and more than 21 billion dollars in spend data, proactive monitoring that surfaces spend optimization and supplier-overlap opportunities, and agentic execution tools including a Renewal Agent and a Proposal Agent that automate contract renewal and negotiation workflows. The platform integrates with more than 75 finance and procurement tools, including Oracle, Workday, QuickBooks, and Salesforce. Tropic positions itself as a buyer-only platform, explicitly stating it maintains no supplier relationships or marketplace kickbacks, differentiating it from vendor-funded procurement marketplaces. The company reports that customers have collectively saved over 425 million dollars, with an average savings of 21 percent per customer, and counts companies such as Zapier, Envoy, and Bennie among its clients. Tropic does not publish self-serve pricing; prospective customers request a demo and receive a custom quote based on company size and spend volume. It competes with procurement and spend-management tools such as Vendr, Zip, and Coupa, differentiating primarily through its buyer-only stance and AI-driven benchmarking and negotiation agents.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '6bc3cd59-7fc3-4389-bfc4-17fcf18c8ed8';

