-- в”Ђв”Ђ TrustArc в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$TrustArc is a privacy management platform that helps enterprises automate cookie and data-subject consent, map and govern data, and obtain third-party privacy certifications like GDPR and CCPA validation.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE(NULL, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(1997, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$201-500 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Walnut Creek, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$TrustArc Review: Enterprise Privacy Compliance Platform$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$TrustArc automates GDPR/CCPA consent, data mapping, and privacy certifications for enterprises. See features, pricing model, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$TrustArc is a privacy compliance software company headquartered in Walnut Creek, California, with roots going back to 1997, when it was founded as TRUSTe, a non-profit industry association created by Lori Fena and Charles Jennings to help online businesses self-regulate privacy practices. In 2000, TRUSTe became the first organization to join the Safe Harbor Principles governing data transfers between the US and EU. The organization transitioned from a non-profit to a venture-backed for-profit company in 2008 with capital from Accel Partners, and rebranded from TRUSTe to TrustArc in 2017 to reflect its shift toward enterprise privacy management software. Bregal Sagemount acquired a substantial stake in 2019, and the company was sold to Main Capital Partners in 2025. Today TrustArc serves roughly 1,500 customers, including large brands such as Abbott, ADP, GE, Nike, and Starbucks. Its platform is organized into three product lines: Privacy Studio, which automates cookie consent, consent and preference management, and data subject rights requests; Governance Suite, which centralizes data mapping, risk assessments, and regulatory research through its Nymity database of more than 800 templates; and Assurance Services, which provides third-party privacy certifications covering GDPR, CCPA/CPRA, the Data Privacy Framework, and other international standards. An AI-powered layer called Arc Intelligence automates parts of the compliance workflow. TrustArc positions itself as a lower-cost, higher-support alternative to OneTrust, the dominant player in the privacy management category, and reports benchmarked customer outcomes including a 35 percent reduction in compliance costs and an 80 percent reduction in privacy incidents. Pricing is entirely custom and requires contacting sales.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '9a7a119c-cb78-4261-9173-2f602bd0dde1';

